Radoslav Dejanović wrote:

> - since there's just a dozen of default administrator usernames and none of 
> them has a password associated with it, it is a child's play to hook on 
> the wireless network and connect to user's computer

Please consider that at least in the default config of Windows XP 
professional, the system does not allow remote connections which are 
authenticated by an account with a blank password. This especially 
includes the entire SMB stuff (RPC, file shares, named pipes) and remote 
desktop connections (Blank Password Restrictions).

References:
http://www.microsoft.com/resources/documentation/windows/xp/all/reskit/en-us/prdp_log_tyry.asp
http://www.microsoft.com/technet/prodtechnol/winxppro/evaluate/xpsec.mspx

